        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 2 at 5:21PM PDT by NWS Hanford CA</headline>
        <description>At 521 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 12
miles south of Tioga Pass, or 13 miles west of June Lake. This
thunderstorm was nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Merced Lake High Sierra Camp, Vogelsang High Sierra Camp, and Merced
Lake Ranger Station.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
